{"TopicId":185801,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Joystick Axis Bug","CreatedByName":"Gavin786","CreatedById":196260,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-24T17:14:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gavin786","CreatedById":196260,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-24T17:14:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJoystick Axis Bug:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xOxSWHqPwe8?start=138\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-07-05T10:46:11Z\u0022 title=\u002207/05/2019 10:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 5, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Gavin786\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-25T05:07:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like you have the RPM controlled by the joystick \u003Cu\u003Eincrementally\u003C/u\u003E (as would be appropriate for a keyboard or button)\u00A0and not \u003Cu\u003Eabsolutely\u003C/u\u003E (as would be appropriate for\u00A0 a pot).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a symbol to the right of the \u0027RPM limit\u0027 entry in the \u0027Group Actions\u0027 column where you probably want to select the level-bars setting,\u00A0not the\u00A0rising staircase.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI cannot test\u00A0 to be sure, because I do not use joysticks, so I hope\u00A0a joystick user will reply soon to say how they use axis groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMain Throttle always uses \u0027Absolute Control\u0027 because that is a slider for both keyboard (using four keys) and mouse users.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-25T07:41:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003EIdentical topics merged and trimmed.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gavin786","CreatedById":196260,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-25T09:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nI actually just found the control.\u00A0 It is on the Custom1 axis itself.\u00A0 It is a tiny graphical checkbox below the control.\u00A0 Very easy to miss!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nThank you KerikBalm.\u00A0 I have been looking for a way to do this for days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nEven made a video asking for help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nThat is going to be super useful in my builds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nGavin786\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}